  <explnote id="DLM2454508" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" pco.suffix="0002" stage="published" year="2009" raised.by="Government" sop.no="69">
    <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
    <para>
      <text>This Supplementary Order Paper modifies the application of the proceeds of sale of vehicles sold under the Sentencing Act 2002 or the Summary Proceedings Act 1957 by requiring any outstanding levies payable under the Sentencing Act 2002 to be paid out of those proceeds. The levies will rank below any outstanding reparation payments and above any outstanding fines.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <text>The Supplementary Order Paper alsoâ€”</text>
      <list>
        <item>
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>requires Registrars to include applicants among the persons who are notified of the cancellation of a written caution:</text>
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>includes offences against the Land Transport Management Act 2003 in the definition of traffic offence:</text>
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
          <para>
            <text>makes a number of referential corrections.</text>
          </para>
        </item>
      </list>
    </para>
  </explnote>
</sop>
